Configurations for systems and distributions; see:

    - [Inventory basics: formats, hosts, and groups](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/inventory_guide/intro_inventory.html#inventory-basics-formats-hosts-and-groups)
    - [Splitting Out Host and Group Specific Data](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/2.7/user_guide/intro_inventory.html#splitting-out-host-and-group-specific-data)

For systems, use `Linux.yml` and `Darwin.yml`. For distros, use e.g. `Fedora.yml` and `MacOSX.yml`.
